Theorem: Set is Subset of Union

Proof:


{{begin-eqn}}
{{eqn | l = x \in S
      | o = \leadsto
      | r = x \in S \land x \in T
      | c = [[Rule of Addition]]
}}
{{eqn | o = \leadsto
      | r = x \in S \cup T
      | c = {{Defof|Set Union}}
}}
{{eqn | o = \leadsto
      | r = S \subset S \cup T
      | c = {{Defof|Subset}}
}}
{{end-eqn}}
Similarly for $T$.
{{qed}}


