Theorem: Set Difference of Complements

Proof:

{{begin-eqn}}
{{eqn | l=\complement \left({S}\right) \setminus \complement \left({T}\right)
      | r=\left\{ {x: x \in \complement \left({S}\right) \land x \notin \complement \left({T}\right)}\right\}
      | c=[[Definition:Set Difference|Definition of Set Difference]]
}}
{{eqn | r=\left\{ {x: x \notin S \land x \in T}\right\}
      | c=[[Definition:Set Complement|Definition of Complement]]
}}
{{eqn | r=\left\{ {x: x \in T \land x \notin S}\right\}
      | c=[[Rule of Commutation]]
}}
{{eqn | r=T \setminus S
