Theorem: Set Difference with Set Difference

Proof:

{{begin-eqn}}
{{eqn | l = S \setminus \paren {S \setminus T}
      | r = \paren {S \setminus S} \cup \paren {S \cap T}
      | c = [[Set Difference with Set Difference is Union of Set Difference with Intersection]]
}}
{{eqn | r = \O \cup \paren {S \cap T}
      | c = [[Set Difference with Self is Empty Set]]
}}
{{eqn | r = S \cap T
      | c = [[Union with Empty Set]]
}}
{{end-eqn}}
Interchanging $S$ and $T$:
{{begin-eqn}}
{{eqn | l = T \setminus \paren {T \setminus S}
      | r = T \cap S
}}
{{eqn | r = S \cap T
      | c = [[Intersection is Commutative]]
}}
{{end-eqn}}
{{qed}}

