By definition of [[Definition:Trivial Relation|trivial relation]], $x \in S \land y \in S \implies x \mathcal R y$. So:
{{begin-eqn}}
{{eqn | l=x_1, x_2, y_1, y_2
      | o=\in
      | r=S
      | c=
}}
{{eqn | ll=\implies
