Theorem: Max and Min are Commutative

Proof:

To simplify our notation:
: Let $\max \left({x, y}\right)$ be (temporarily) denoted $x \overline \wedge y$
: Let $\min \left({x, y}\right)$ be (temporarily) denoted $x \underline \vee y$.
